column5: Well after a long and uneventful archery season, gun season finally opened today here in ohio. started the morning watching a young button buck, followed by some fork horns and then this nice 10 point buck. After tagging him i took a nice plump doe about a half hour later.      so far that makes three on the year for me, i can still take three more doe's if i can. lots of jerky and vinison steaks in the near future.  jason
Nice...a bunch of my chums are at top of the caves this week
nice buck. I like the kicker off the back.
Nice start Jason.  It's part of your payback for all the corn you've donated.
thanks guys, yeah i like that lil kicker too
